cidrBlock.description: The IPv4 network range to allow or deny, in CIDR notation. The specified CIDR block is modified to its canonical form. For example, `100.68.0.18/18` will be converted to `100.68.0.0/18`.

icmpTypeCode.description: Defines the ICMP protocol that consists of the ICMP type and code. Defined below.

portRange.description: Range of ports the rule applies to. Defined below.

protocol.description: Protocol number. A value of `1` means all the protocols.

ruleAction.description: Indicates whether to `allow` or `deny` the traffic that matches the rule.

ruleNumber.description: Rule number for the entry. All the network ACL entries are processed in ascending order by rule number.
